{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "12", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "14", "S": "08"}}, "news": [{"title": "DB Ozone shops got OC despite missing MMRDA NOC, shows RTI", "para": "Residents of DB Ozone housing project face delays in receiving occupation certificates for their homes. Commercial spaces within the same project have obtained occupancy clearance and are operational. This comes as the developer, Neel Kamal Realtors, has outstanding obligations under the state's Rental Housing Scheme. Legal interventions and court orders highlight the ongoing dispute over project completion and compliance.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/retail/occupancy-controversy-db-ozone-shops-obtain-certificates-despite-lack-of-mmrda-clearance/131673131?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-134265/131673131.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "retail"}, {"title": "Plot-wise ready reckoner rates in Nagpur within two years: Maharashtra government", "para": "Maharashtra's Revenue Minister announced a new micro-zoning system for Ready Reckoner rates, aiming to end uniform valuations within localities. This property-by-property survey, starting in Mumbai, will assign distinct rates based on infrastructure and amenities, differentiating between slum dwellings, standalone homes, and high-rises. The initiative, driven by the CM and public demand, promises fairer property valuations across the state.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtra-government-to-revolutionize-realty-valuations-in-nagpur-with-micro-zoning/131673045?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26844/131673045.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "DDA warns architects, engineers & owners against lying about building plans", "para": "Delhi